>Sapient Quadrupeds
Primary setting, they don't exist.
Secondary setting, they do. Basically, you have humans, animals, and anthros. Anthros are genetic chimeras - mating with an animal of the same species produces a intelligent but non-sapient animal that looks identical to the animal and is genetically the animal. Anthro + human produces a mendelian split between anthro, human, and half breed, though the anthro half is regressive.
As for the how, that's not going to be common knowledge in-universe. Once I have a good excuse, I'll have the first story.

>Anthro Casual Nudity
Primary setting, it's happened historically, but rare now unless sunbathing.
Secondary, you wouldn't dare. It'd be like screaming epithets in the ghetto.

>Bird Waifur- Waifeathers?
Secondary setting, it'll be possible, but I don't have plans for it yet. I'll be cribbing from something outside of here - it's not necessary for a given form to be workable in modern society. The further you get from a form that can be anthro-ized, the less accepted.

>Genetic traits
Primary setting, no hybrids. In fact, without inoculations during childhood, it's possible to die from contact. Usually this requires sexual contact, but possible without in rare cases.
Secondary setting, see above. The bonus will be that I'm not following the same rules as my primary setting. I'm already planning a 96" tall mare, and a 44" tall mare. So it'll be inevitable that I'll be aiming for something horrific rather than cheap fetish fuel.

>Sapient Quadrupeds
Nay, or at least have them able to learn bipedal movement, I want them to be capable of integration into a regular human society
>Anthro Casual Nudity
Nay, even though it would probably make sense for most anthro species to not need to wear clothes because their natural coats would give them the protection they need, it feels like clothing is an important part of higher level intelligence and societies and that any species that became truly sapient would begin to desire clothing
>Bird Waifur- Waifeathers?
Either is fine, though I imagine feathers would become less pronounced over time due to bird anthros' inability to take flight lessening their need for an aerodynamically designed part of their body, but other than that, probably mostly the same as above

>Sapient Quadrupeds
I can into various taurs. But, if anthro with only four limbs, I require bipeds with dexterous, human-ish hands (retractable claws are fine). I can go with a lot of different feet designs so long as functional and on-model for the species. Human-ish feet are fine as a default in bipeds, but taurs should be closer to their genetic design.

>Anthro Casual Nudity
I'm in favor of casual nudity, all species. Humans included. Individuals who wish to wear clothes, it's up to them. Fashions will evolve and cycle. Mandatory clothing is a sin against personal freedom and is unacceptable policy.

>Bird Waifur- Waifeathers?
NOPE. Just me. I'm specieist. Avaians are cool from afar and people who are into them, it's their business. Same with scalies. But neither for me. Or fish. I like my mamalian furred waifurs.

>Genetic traits
Tough call. This is a world-building issue, and genetics are complicated. It's easy to say humans and catgirls can breed, and design their offspring. What happens three generations later when a child is born of bat, cat, human, horse, dog, and raccoon lineage ..?

On the other hand, I like a world where species only breed to species. You can sex your waifur all day every day any time of day without protection and never worry. Nice freedom to have. When it's time for a planned family, she can be artificially inseminated, or breed with her own species, or adoption. Same if you want a human child.

I also like the idea that a waifur can carry the child of any.most species, so she could be impregnated with an embryo of any compatible species. This might be the best option in the end. Any couple can raise children born to your waifur from a wide variety of species, and that makes for a cool world with a lot of diversity and a lot of people/anthros growing up in mixed families. A lot less racism.

So, I lean strongly toward genetically pure species-to-species breeding and very rare genetic hybrid options.
